g = \sum_\pi\sigma(\pi) \prod_i g_{i\pi(i)}.
\frac{\partial g}{\partial x^l} = \sum_\pi \sigma(\pi) \sum_i \frac{\partial g_{i\pi(i)}}{\partial x^l} \prod_{j \ne i} g_{j\pi(j)} \\ =\sum_{ik} \frac{\partial g_{ik}}{\partial x^l}\sum_{\pi:\pi(i)=k} \prod_{j\ne i}\sigma(\pi) g_{j\pi(j)} \\ =\sum_{ik} \frac{\partial g_{ik}}{\partial x^l} g \ g^{ki}. 
